   This is a freshwater pond in       
Stanmore RAF base. It was formed      
naturally and has never been in any   
way cultivated. The water was found to
contain the following organisms:      
CYCLOPS _ found about 1.5 metres from 
the bank, approximately 2mm. long;    
RAMSHORN SNAIL _ rare in this pond;   
SMALL POND LEECH _ found amongst      
plants very near the edge of the pond;
WHIRLIGIG BEETLE _ found spinning and 
drifting on the surface;              
WATER CRICKET _ found  skimming over  
the still parts of the pond surface;  
NYMPH _ found swimming on the surface;
GREAT POND SNAIL _ very common;       
WATER WORM _ found in bottom mud;     
WATER SKATER _ found scavenging among 
plants;                               
COMMON WATER FLEA _ very common,      
darting about at high speed.          
Average of 82.3 species per 5cc.
